snippet: An assisted suicide charge was dismissed Tuesday against a nurse accused of handing her terminally ill father a bottle of morphine.
abstract: Assisted suicide charge against Philadelphia nurse Barbara Mancini, accused of handing her terminally ill father a bottle of morphine, is dismissed after prosecutors fail to prove crime occurred.
lead_paragraph: An assisted suicide charge was dismissed Tuesday against a nurse accused of handing her terminally ill father a bottle of morphine.
